  "text": "The first step of the presented approach is the definition of a user segment. User segment is a subset of users, web site's visitors, which share a common characteristic. Simple examples of standard market segments are breakdown of users by gender or age [CITATION_1] . More complex segmentation can involve income, job or industry, interests a combination of these. The context from the access logs provides additional segments that are relevant to a web site, such as users coming from search engines (e.g. Google, Bing) or social networks (e.g. Facebook, Twitter), users also reading about traveling, users from particular country or city, etc.",
